fields.description:
It's possible to create a build configuration with properties to be substituted such as a maven builder with the goal -
{noformat}
clean verify -Pclover-optimize,clover-optimize-bamboo -Djava.io.tmpdir=${bamboo.capability.tmpdir} -Dhttp.port=${bamboo.capability.http.port} -Dcargo.rmi.port=${bamboo.capability.rmi.port}
{noformat}

As the build starts, a verification that the agent's configuration has substituted values for all properties could be performed and a more meaningful failure given than we currently get (see https://bamboo.extranet.atlassian.com/browse/CONFFUNC-OPTIMIZED-1569 as an example). Perhaps verification could be performed even earlier such as during configuration where you check that all valid agents have all necessary properties set (although I guess agents can be added later and the validation would need to also be triggered then...)

e.g. when I hit:

http://localhost:8085/bamboo/admin/administer.action

access log shows:

{quote}
2009-11-09 09:03:53,943 INFO [1854355354@qtp-2013238005-17] [AccessLogFilter] admin http://localhost:8085/bamboo/admin/administer.action 89682kb
2009-11-09 09:03:55,140 INFO [1146963006@qtp-2013238005-15] [AccessLogFilter] admin http://localhost:8085/bamboo/admin/java%20script:false; 75052kb
{quote}

some rougue javascript somewhere is accessing:

{noformat}
java.script:false;
{noformat}
